        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 25 at 7:25PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 725 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Lefors, or 10 miles southeast of Pampa, moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lefors.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 100 AM CDT for
the Panhandle of Texas.</instruction>
